# Root .dockerignore — the production image builds from the repo-root context
# (docker-compose `app` service, context: .). The backend's own .dockerignore is
# NOT consulted from a root context, so everything excluded from the build image
# must be listed here. Keep manifests + lockfile + source IN; keep installs,
# build outputs, secrets, and the Python services OUT.

# Dependencies / installs (re-created by `pnpm install` in the build stage)
**/node_modules
.pnpm-store

# Build outputs
**/dist
**/build
ayunis-core-backend/frontend
ayunis-core-backend/coverage
**/.nyc_output

# Secrets & local env
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/.env.example
# Exception: the frontend .env must enter the build context so Vite can inline its
# VITE_* vars at build time. Being part of the context (vs a secret mount, whose
# contents BuildKit excludes from the cache key) is what makes a changed value
# correctly bust the frontend build layer. It only lands in the discarded build
# stage — the production image copies the built dist, never the .env. The backend
# .env stays excluded (the backend reads its env at runtime via compose env_file).
!ayunis-core-frontend/.env

# Python services (not part of the JS image; built by their own Dockerfiles)
ayunis-core-code-execution
ayunis-core-anonymize

# VCS / tooling / local dev
.git
.github
.husky
.dev
.claude
.agents
.pi
scripts
*.md

# Logs & OS cruft
**/*.log
**/.DS_Store
**/uploads
